attributes.gcd: Refers to the unique identifier of the account or contract held by the customer. Account number is defined as numbers, letters or alphanumeric code assigned to every significant customer, supplier and lender for ease of reference in accounting records of the financial institution.
Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.
Refers to a unique Code representing a particular Instrument. This code can be ISIN Code, CUSIP, SEDOL etc. Instrument Contract dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

attributes.logicalName: Offset Account Held By Customer Indicator
attributes.gcd: Refers to, if offset account is held by customer. Allowed values are Y : Yes, N : No.

Refers to the account number that is being offset. It Refers to the loan account number which this liability account is offsetting. There can be multiple savings account offsetting a loan, but a liability account would not offset more than one loan account. For hypothecated deposits, it Refers to the account number of the related loan that is used to net against the deposit.
Refers to the short position of offset account . Allowed values are S : Short, L: Long.

Refers to the manner in which the Oracle client holds the offset security position associated with this position pair. List of Values are C: Cash, M: Margin, S: Short, V: Versus Payment, R: Repurchase Agreement, L: Reverse Repurchase Agreement or On Loan, X: Express Credit, I: Income, N: Non-Purpose Loan, O: Other.
Refers to the security associated with the offset position in this position pair.
Refers to the number of units (for example, shares or contracts) held in the offset position associated with this position pair.

attributes.logicalName: Offsetting Performance Based Swap Derivative Indicator
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Firm Longs where the sale coincides with an offsetting performance-based swap derivative.

Refers to the nature of the relationship between the two positions in this pair. E.g. Bullish Spread, Bearish Spread, Covered Call, Covered Put, Credit Spread, Debit Spread, Time Spread, Short Straddle, Long Straddle, Uncovered etc.

Refers to credit derivative Position held by the entity or the manner in which the owner holds the primary security position associated with this position pair, for example, on a cash basis, on margin, or versus payment. It can have values as Long or Short where long position indicates Credit protection bought and short position indicates credit protection sold.
Refers to the unique code assigned to each of the Products offered by the Bank.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.

This column stores the number of units, for example, shares or contracts of the specified
security being transferred via this transaction.
